content.description:
This route starts 40 feet right of ‘medicine Man’. 

Pitch 1: Climb up the blocky corner system into a tiered section of overlapping rock to a stance. Belay here. 

Pitch 2: Exit left and up toward the large roof at the widest section below a hanging corner. Climb into the overhang reaching left for a hidden hold. Work your way left and into a hanging dihedral. Continue climb up over the next overhang capping what’s below. Continue up the slabs above to the top.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description: Look for the large white buttress with several roof systems on it. Start by climbing the left-facing arete wit ha roof at its top. Continue climbing up in the small dihedral and up to the top.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description:
This route starts 20 feet right of ‘Warpath’. 

Pitch 1: Climb up the sketchy rock to a belay ledge just below a roof. Belay here. 

Pitch 2: Exit up through the crux overhanging roof and then up the face to the top.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description:
This is a variation of the previous route but fun! 

Pitch 1: Same first portion of the first pitch as ‘Slacker’s Ceiling’ but climb the thin upper seam through the overhanging roof and onto the slab then up the belay. 

Pitch 2: Same as previous route.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description:
Pitch 1: Climb the same first pitch as 'Slacker's Ceiling'

 Pitch 2: 5 feet right of the roof is another roof with a finger crack. Climb the roof then up the finger crack then head up and right to a belay at a tree.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description: There used to be a large uprooted tree signifying this route but its since rotted away. Look for the white buttress. This route starts 10 feet to the left of that feature. Climb up the blocky corners then onto a tiered slab below a roof. Pull the crux roof on the left of the narrow section then up right onto the slabs to the top.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description: This route starts 2 feet to the right of ‘Slammer Jam’. Climb up through a notch then up the quartz veined roof system to the top.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description: Continue further up the baseline trail and the rock will become of lesser quality. The trail steepens quite a bit. In this section are some great routes! This wall is about 350 feet further uphill from ‘Death Don’t Have No Mercy’. There’s a low angle inset surrounded by several low overhangs.
